ARCHITECTURE.md
     1Ôćĺ# Architecture
     3Ôćĺ> Document is a work in progress!
     4Ôćĺ
     5ÔćĺÔîśK is born from a simple constraint: can you write a combobox with filtering and sorting using the [compound component](https://kentcdodds.com/blog/compound-components-with-react-hooks) approach? We didn't want to render items manually from an array:
     6Ôćĺ
     7Ôćĺ```tsx
     8Ôćĺ// No
     9Ôćĺ<>
    10Ôćĺ  {items.map((item) => {
    11Ôćĺ    return <div>{item}</div>
    12Ôćĺ  })}
    13Ôćĺ</>
    14Ôćĺ```
    15Ôćĺ
    16ÔćĺWe didn't want to provide a render prop:
    17Ôćĺ
    18Ôćĺ```tsx
    19Ôćĺ// No
    20ÔćĺonItemRender={({ item }) => {
    21Ôćĺ  return <div>{item}</div>
    22Ôćĺ}}
    23Ôćĺ```
    24Ôćĺ
    25ÔćĺInstead, we wanted to render components:
    26Ôćĺ
    27Ôćĺ```tsx
    28Ôćĺ// Yes
    29Ôćĺ<Item>My item</Item>
    30Ôćĺ```
    31Ôćĺ
    32ÔćĺEspecially, we wanted full component composition:
    33Ôćĺ
    34Ôćĺ```tsx
    35Ôćĺ// YES
    36Ôćĺ<>
    37Ôćĺ  <BlogItems />
    38Ôćĺ  {staticItems}
    39Ôćĺ</>
    40Ôćĺ```
    41Ôćĺ
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    46Ôćĺ## Approach
    48ÔćĺÔîśK always keeps every item and group rendered in the React tree. Each item and group adds or removes itself from the DOM based on the search input. The DOM is authoritative.┬áItem selection order is based on the DOM order, which is based on the React render order, which the consumer provides.
    49Ôćĺ
    50Ôćĺ### Discarded approach
    52ÔćĺWe did not use `React.Children` iteration because it will not support component composition. There is no way to "peek inside" the items contained within `<BlogItems />`, so those items cannot be filtered.
    53Ôćĺ
    54ÔćĺWe did not use an object-based data array for each item, like `{ name: "Logout", action: () => logout() }` because this is strict and limiting. In reality, the interface of those objects grows with edge-cases, like `image`, `detailedSubTitle`, `hideWhenRootSearch`, etc. We prefer that you have full control of item rendering, including icons, keyboard shortcuts, and styling. Don't want an item shown? Don't render it. Only want to show an item under condition xyz? Render it.
    55Ôćĺ
    56ÔćĺWe did not use a render prop because they are an inelegant pattern and quickly fall to long, centralised if-else logic chains. For example, if you want a fancy sparkle rainbow item, you need a new if statement to render that item specially.
    57Ôćĺ
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    60Ôćĺ## Example
    62Ôćĺ```tsx
    63Ôćĺ<Input value="b" />
    64Ôćĺ<List>
    65Ôćĺ  <Item>A</Item>
    66Ôćĺ  <Item>B</Item>
    67Ôćĺ</List>
    68Ôćĺ```
    69Ôćĺ
    70ÔćĺThe "A" item should not be shown! But we cannot remove it from the React tree, because the user controls it. In most cases, this is easy because the rendered items is sourced from a backing data array:
    71Ôćĺ
    72Ôćĺ```tsx
    73Ôćĺ<>
    74Ôćĺ  {['A', 'B'].map((item) => {
    75Ôćĺ    if (matches(item, search)) {
    76Ôćĺ      return <Item>{item}</Item>
    77Ôćĺ    }
    78Ôćĺ  })}
    79Ôćĺ</>
    80Ôćĺ```
    81Ôćĺ
    82ÔćĺBut in our case, the item will remain in the React tree and just be removed from the DOM:
    83Ôćĺ
    84Ôćĺ```tsx
    85Ôćĺ<List>
    86Ôćĺ  {/* returns `null`, no DOM created */}
    87Ôćĺ  <Item>A</Item>
    88Ôćĺ  <Item>B</Item>
    89Ôćĺ</List>
    90Ôćĺ```
    91Ôćĺ
    92Ôćĺ## Performance
    94ÔćĺThis is more expensive memory wise, because if there are 2,000 items but the list is filtered to only 2 items, we still allocate memory for 2,000 instances of the Item component. But it's our only option! Thankfully we can still keep the DOM size to 2 items.
    95Ôćĺ
    96Ôćĺ## Groups
    98ÔćĺItem mount informs both the root and the parent group, which keeps track of items within it. Each group informs the root.
README.md
     5Ôćĺ# ÔîśK
     7ÔćĺÔîśK is a command menu React component that can also be used as an accessible combobox. You render items, it filters and sorts them automatically. ÔîśK supports a fully composable API <sup><sup>[How?](/ARCHITECTURE.md)</sup></sup>, so you can wrap items in other components or even as static JSX.
     8Ôćĺ
     9Ôćĺ## Install
    11Ôćĺ```bash
    12Ôćĺpnpm install cmdk
    13Ôćĺ```
    14Ôćĺ
    15Ôćĺ## Use
    17Ôćĺ```tsx
    18Ôćĺimport { Command } from 'cmdk'
    19Ôćĺ
    20Ôćĺconst CommandMenu = () => {
    21Ôćĺ  return (
    22Ôćĺ    <Command label="Command Menu">
    23Ôćĺ      <Command.Input />
    24Ôćĺ      <Command.List>
    25Ôćĺ        <Command.Empty>No results found.</Command.Empty>
    26Ôćĺ
    27Ôćĺ        <Command.Group heading="Letters">
    28Ôćĺ          <Command.Item>a</Command.Item>
    29Ôćĺ          <Command.Item>b</Command.Item>
    30Ôćĺ          <Command.Separator />
    31Ôćĺ          <Command.Item>c</Command.Item>
    32Ôćĺ        </Command.Group>
    33Ôćĺ
    34Ôćĺ        <Command.Item>Apple</Command.Item>
    35Ôćĺ      </Command.List>
    36Ôćĺ    </Command>
    37Ôćĺ  )
    38Ôćĺ}
    39Ôćĺ```
    40Ôćĺ
    41ÔćĺOr in a dialog:
    42Ôćĺ
    43Ôćĺ```tsx
    44Ôćĺimport { Command } from 'cmdk'
    45Ôćĺ
    46Ôćĺconst CommandMenu = () => {
    47Ôćĺ  const [open, setOpen] = React.useState(false)
    48Ôćĺ
    49Ôćĺ  // Toggle the menu when ÔîśK is pressed
    50Ôćĺ  React.useEffect(() => {
    51Ôćĺ    const down = (e) => {
    52Ôćĺ      if (e.key === 'k' && (e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey)) {
    53Ôćĺ        e.preventDefault()
    54Ôćĺ        setOpen((open) => !open)
    55Ôćĺ      }
    56Ôćĺ    }
    57Ôćĺ
    58Ôćĺ    document.addEventListener('keydown', down)
    59Ôćĺ    return () => document.removeEventListener('keydown', down)
    60Ôćĺ  }, [])
    61Ôćĺ
    62Ôćĺ  return (
    63Ôćĺ    <Command.Dialog open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen} label="Global Command Menu">
    64Ôćĺ      <Command.Input />
    65Ôćĺ      <Command.List>
    66Ôćĺ        <Command.Empty>No results found.</Command.Empty>
    67Ôćĺ
    68Ôćĺ        <Command.Group heading="Letters">
    69Ôćĺ          <Command.Item>a</Command.Item>
    70Ôćĺ          <Command.Item>b</Command.Item>
    71Ôćĺ          <Command.Separator />
    72Ôćĺ          <Command.Item>c</Command.Item>
    73Ôćĺ        </Command.Group>
    74Ôćĺ
    75Ôćĺ        <Command.Item>Apple</Command.Item>
    76Ôćĺ      </Command.List>
    77Ôćĺ    </Command.Dialog>
    78Ôćĺ  )
    79Ôćĺ}
    80Ôćĺ```
    81Ôćĺ
    82Ôćĺ## Parts and styling
    84ÔćĺAll parts forward props, including `ref`, to an appropriate element. Each part has a specific data-attribute (starting with `cmdk-`) that can be used for styling.
    85Ôćĺ
    86Ôćĺ### Command `[cmdk-root]` ÔÇŽ
