   430Ôćĺ## FAQ
   432Ôćĺ**Accessible?** Yes. Labeling, aria attributes, and DOM ordering tested with Voice Over and Chrome DevTools. [Dialog](#dialog-cmdk-dialog-cmdk-overlay) composes an accessible Dialog implementation.
   433Ôćĺ
   434Ôćĺ**Virtualization?** No. Good performance up to 2,000-3,000 items, though. Read below to bring your own.
   435Ôćĺ
   436Ôćĺ**Filter/sort items manually?** Yes. Pass `shouldFilter={false}` to [Command](#command-cmdk-root). Better memory usage and performance. Bring your own virtualization this way.
   437Ôćĺ
   438Ôćĺ**React 18 safe?** Yes, required. Uses React 18 hooks like `useId` and `useSyncExternalStore`.
   439Ôćĺ
   440Ôćĺ**Unstyled?** Yes, use the listed CSS selectors.
   441Ôćĺ
   442Ôćĺ**Hydration mismatch?** No, likely a bug in your code. Ensure the `open` prop to `Command.Dialog` is `false` on the server.
   443Ôćĺ
   444Ôćĺ**React strict mode safe?** Yes. Open an issue if you notice an issue.
   445Ôćĺ
   446Ôćĺ**Weird/wrong behavior?** Make sure your `Command.Item` has a `key` and unique `value`.
   447Ôćĺ
   448Ôćĺ**Concurrent mode safe?** Maybe, but concurrent mode is not yet real. Uses risky approaches like manual DOM ordering.
   449Ôćĺ
   450Ôćĺ**React server component?** No, it's a client component.
   451Ôćĺ
   452Ôćĺ**Listen for ÔîśK automatically?** No, do it yourself to have full control over keybind context.
   453Ôćĺ
   454Ôćĺ**React Native?** No, and no plans to support it. If you build a React Native version, let us know and we'll link your repository here.
   455Ôćĺ
   456Ôćĺ## History
   458ÔćĺWritten in 2019 by Paco ([@pacocoursey](https://twitter.com/pacocoursey)) to see if a composable combobox API was possible. Used for the Vercel command menu and autocomplete by Rauno ([@raunofreiberg](https://twitter.com/raunofreiberg)) in 2020. Re-written independently in 2022 with a simpler and more performant approach. Ideas and help from Shu ([@shuding\_](https://twitter.com/shuding_)).
   459Ôćĺ
   460Ôćĺ[use-descendants](https://github.com/pacocoursey/use-descendants) was extracted from the 2019 version.
   461Ôćĺ
   462Ôćĺ## Testing
   464ÔćĺFirst, install dependencies and Playwright browsers:
   465Ôćĺ
   466Ôćĺ```bash
   467Ôćĺpnpm install
   468Ôćĺpnpm playwright install
   469Ôćĺ```
   470Ôćĺ
   471ÔćĺThen ensure you've built the library:
   472Ôćĺ
   473Ôćĺ```bash
   474Ôćĺpnpm build
   475Ôćĺ```
   476Ôćĺ
   477ÔćĺThen run the tests using your local build against real browser engines:
   478Ôćĺ
   479Ôćĺ```bash
   480Ôćĺpnpm test
   481Ôćĺ```
